## 8. Analysis — What the Numbers Reveal

### 8.1 World Switch Dominates

```
PRINT   = 379 us → world switch overhead
ENCRYPT = ~520 us → world switch + 4KB XOR

Breakdown:
  World switch cost = 379 us  (73% of total)
  Encryption cost   = 141 us  (27% of total)

Key insight:
  Even though we encrypted 4096 bytes in Secure World,
  the world switch itself costs MORE than the actual work.

  This is why TEE APIs are designed to batch operations:
  → One SMC call to process large data = efficient
  → Many SMC calls for small data     = inefficient
```

### 8.2 Throughput Inside S-EL1

```
Encryption of 4096 bytes = 141 us additional cost

Throughput = 4096 bytes / 141 us
           = 4096 / 0.000141 seconds
           = 29,049,645 bytes/second
           = ~29 MB/s

This is OTP (XOR) speed inside S-EL1 on QEMU.
Real hardware with AES hardware accelerator = GB/s range.
```

### 8.3 Context Save Cost Estimation

```
EL3 saves ~30 system registers per world switch
Two world switches per call = 60 register operations

If each register save/restore = ~500ns on QEMU:
  60 × 500 ns = 30,000 ns = 30 us

But we measured 379 us — remaining is:
  379 - 30 = 349 us from other sources:
  → QEMU instruction translation overhead
  → Cache misses
  → Syscall overhead
  → Green TEE mmu_map_range()
```

